how does covid-19 spread? currently, these are the following ways: recent travel to an affected country, a cough or sneeze from a person who is sick, and close contact with a person who is sick. to learn more go to https://health.baltimorecity.gov/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov coronavirus covid19 publichealth
planning to host an event? learn more about the city guidance on events during this time. to learn more go to https://health.baltimorecity.gov/sites/default/files/covid-19_eventguidance2.pdf

traveled to a high-risk country recently? stay home for 14 days and call a doctor if you have a fever and/or cough. to find out what countries are high risk, see the cdc’s recommendation: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/after-travel-precautions.html coronavirus covid19 publichealth coronavirusbalt

protect against the spread of the covid-19 virus by: staying home when you are sick; washing your hands; and avoid close contact like hugs, kisses, handshakes, large crowds, sharing a plate, etc. coronavirus covid19 publichealth coronavirusbalt

try to keep at least six feet away from people and avoid direct physical contact. to learn more go to https://health.baltimorecity.gov/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov coronavirus covid19 publichealth coronavirusbalt

who’s at the highest risk for developing covid-19 as a severe illness? older adults who are 60 and older, and people with underlying conditions such as heart disease, lung disease, or diabetes. this population should take extra precautions. coronavirus covid19 publichealth

unsure what covid-19 symptoms are? look for the following: cough, fever over 100.4f, and shortness of breath. to learn more go to https://health.baltimorecity.gov/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov coronavirus covid19 publichealth coronavirusbalt
